casebody.data:
Lisa Janette EARLEYWINE, Respondent,
v.
Ehren Larry EARLEYWINE, Appellant. WD 81330 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Filed: December 18, 2018 Helen L. Wade, Columbia, for appellant. Edward C. Clausen, Kimberly Guthrie, Jefferson City, for respondent. Before Division One: Lisa White Hardwick, Presiding Judge, Edward R. Ardini, Jr., And Thomas N. Chapman, Judges

ORDER

Per Curiam

Ehren Earleywine appeals from the judgment dissolving his marriage to Lisa Earleywine. He contends the circuit court erred in awarding maintenance. Upon review of the briefs and the record, we find no error and affirm the judgment. We have provided the parties with a Memorandum explaining the reasons for our decision, because a published opinion would have no precedential value.

AFFIRMED. Rule 84.16(b).
